  "texts": [
    "250 Alowais et al. [269] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" refers to the tendency of AIgenerated data and/or analysis to fabricate and create false information that cannot be supported by existing evidence, even though it may appear realistic and convincing.",
    "251 Liu et al. [270] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" can be defined as the capability of LLM-based chatbots to convey false information as though it were true.",
    "252 Xie et al. [271] 2023 Health \"AI hallucination\" refers to when a medical AI system is considered unfaithful or to have a factual inconsistency issue, as it generates content that is not supported by existing knowledge, reference, or data.",
    "Intrinsic Error: The generated output contradicts with existing knowledge, reference, or data.",
    "Extrinsic Error: The generated output cannot be confirmed (either supported or contradicted) by existing knowledge, reference, or data."
  ],
